Class StatementParser

  • public class StatementParser
extends AbstractParser<AbstractSyntaxAST>
    A AbstractParser for the AbstractStatementSyntaxAST with which you can easily parse the AbstractStatementSyntaxAST or check if the current AbstractToken and parent AbstractSyntaxAST are capable to parse a new AbstractStatementSyntaxAST.

      • canParse

        public boolean canParse(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                        SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        Tests if the current AbstractToken is capable to parse a new AbstractStatementSyntaxAST. Depending of the parent AbstractSyntaxAST it will check for different values of the previously checked IdentifierToken. So you can't declare a ThisStatementSyntaxAST if the parent already is a ThisStatementSyntaxAST.
        Specified by:
        canParse in class AbstractParser<AbstractSyntaxAST>
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the AbstractSyntaxAST in which this AST is getting parsed.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used to call methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) etc.
        Returns:
        false if the current AbstractToken and parent AbstractSyntaxAST aren't capable to parse a new AbstractStatementSyntaxAST or true if they do.
